file_content.text: It's clear Darth Baras failed to inform you exactly who you'd be crossing. This demonstration should make up for that deficiency.
Ahhhhhggggg!
You want Agent Dellocon, you want me, I won't be hard to find anymore.
I'm on the roof of the satellite platform in Network Access. If you dare show, I will grant you a duel to the death. Be honored.
My lord, if I may, I smell an ambush.
Commander Naughlen and his men owe me their lives. I mean to collect. Hail him, now.
I can bring my own army.
Put that military mind of yours to work and thwart Rathari's ambush.
You will plan the assault.
Yes, my lord. If I'm right, I recommend having numbers at the ready.
Halidrell's forces have been wiped out, but there is another solution.
Let him ambush me. He'll find out I'm more than his match.
I'll handle whatever he tries.
I make no suggestion of fear, my lord. But I suggest a countermove to thwart his gambit.
You wisely leveraged an alliance with Republic Commander Naughlen. You might call upon him and his men.
You continue to prove yourself a valuable asset to me. Hail Commander Naughlen.
Brilliant, Captain.
I will not share the glory of Rathari's destruction with the Republic.
He doesn't deserve this honor.
Of course, my lord. Then I will assist you to the best of my ability.
I will relish turning the tables on Rathari. Get Commander Naughlen on the holo immediately.
That gives me sinister joy.
I find that military mind of yours very attractive, Quinn. Call Commander Naughlen.
[Flirt] You're so impressive.
Yes, my lord. Patching him through now.
My lord, there's a high probability that this is a trap. I suggest caution.
I'm ready, whatever he has up his sleeve.
Caution is not my style.
Quinn, always looking out for me. Is it love? Desire?
[Flirt] Worried about me?
Love of duty, perhaps. Desire for victory. I cannot speak beyond that.
Your advice and strategic senses are a great help to me.
Thank you, Captain.
Your success is my reward.
Tell me something I don't already know.
No kidding.
Apologies, my lord. One can be too thorough.
I will assist you any way possible in the battle to come.
Hah, he's a moron if he thinks we're gonna walk into such an obvious ambush... right?
Commander Naughlen and his men owe me their lives. Hail him. I want to collect.
We'll walk in with an army.
Rathari is my mission, so I'll withstand whatever trap he springs.
We have no other choice.
Guess that means I will too.
I'll take every precaution.
Don't worry.
Hey wait--what about that Republic commander guy who's butt you saved? He owes you one.
That's all I ask. Not like we can avoid going after the guy.
You can stay and hide here if you're afraid.
Coward.
Not afraid just want to be smart--hey, what about calling that Republic commander guy you saved before? He owes you.
Now you're thinking, Vette. Hail him.
Good idea.
Happy to do my part. Here you go.
Goodie, I get to play secretary. Here you go.
You're so attractive when you think on your feet, Vette. Hail Commander Naughlen.
[Flirt] I could kiss you.
Gladly. And--uh--thanks for the compliment.
The glory of the kill will be mine and mine alone.
I don't need him.
I know better than to think that means I don't have to join you.
Do you think I need you to come up with my strategies, Vette?
Quiet. Already planning that.
Just trying to help. I'll hail the commander for you.
I had a feeling you'd call, Sith. Can't say I'm looking forward to this.
Keep your insecurity to yourself, Commander.
Stop being squeamish.
I only hope that what you ask will not undermine the Republic.
You should be pleased to wipe the slate clean between us, Commander.
You're getting off easy.
Believe me, I am. I just don't relish being obligated to do my enemy's bidding.
I'm about to give you the opportunity for glory few have seen--the destruction of a Sith Lord!
Ready yourself for greatness.
That's unexpected. You've definitely piqued my interest.
A soldier pays his debts. Tell me what must be done.
Not afraid, just not keen on striding into certain doom without a plan.
All right, let's see what's waiting for us, then.
